  "prompt": "How do I get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets?",
  "response": "To get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log in to your IRCTC account:**\n   - Visit the IRCTC website (www.irctc.co.in) and log in using your username and password.\n\n2. **Navigate to 'My Transactions':**\n   - After logging in, go to the 'My Account' section, and then click on 'My Transactions'.\n\n3. **Select 'Booked Ticket History':**\n   - In the 'My Transactions' menu, you will find an option called 'Booked Ticket History'. Click on this to see a list of all your past bookings.\n\n4. **Find the Desired Ticket:**\n   - Browse through the list to find the journey for which you need the ticket. You can filter by date or journey details to make the search easier.\n\n5. **View and Print the Ticket:**\n   - Once you find the ticket, click on the 'Print E-Ticket' or 'Print' option next to it. This will open a PDF version of your ticket.\n   - Download the PDF and print it from your computer.\n\n**Important Notes:**\n- Ensure you have a working printer and sufficient ink/paper.\n- It's advisable to keep electronic copies of your tickets for future reference.\n\nIf you face any issues during this process, you can contact IRCTC customer support for assistance.",
